468
00:34:20,625 --> 00:34:23,150
Hey, Mick, take over.

469
00:34:35,273 --> 00:34:39,209
- Hey! [Muttering]
- [Laughing]

470
00:34:45,850 --> 00:34:49,183
- Faster, mick!

471
00:35:15,446 --> 00:35:19,439
Hey, everybody!
The lobsters!

472
00:35:22,753 --> 00:35:26,450
[Alida]
Get 'em out of the way. There!

473
00:35:42,039 --> 00:35:44,234
- Mrs. Scott?
- Yes?

474
00:35:44,342 --> 00:35:47,140
I'm Mr. Week. Mrs. Warren told me
you might be interested in television.

475
00:35:47,245 --> 00:35:50,510
Most of my ladies tell me
tv gives them something to do.

476
00:35:50,615 --> 00:35:53,516
Mrs. Warren has made a mistake.
I'm not interested in television.

477
00:35:53,618 --> 00:35:55,609
I'm in a terrible hurry.
Will you excuse me?

478
00:35:55,720 --> 00:35:59,212
May I call again, Mrs. Scott...

479
00:36:30,254 --> 00:36:33,087
When you called me
to hurry, I hurried.

480
00:36:33,191 --> 00:36:36,092
Did you have anything better to do
of a Saturday afternoon?

481
00:36:36,194 --> 00:36:38,958
No, as a matter of fact, the children
aren't coming up this weekend.

482
00:36:39,063 --> 00:36:40,928
After you.

483
00:36:42,066 --> 00:36:43,966
Oooh!

484
00:36:48,306 --> 00:36:50,672
What you've done to it!

485
00:36:51,876 --> 00:36:56,813
And the fireplace!
Oh, it's so friendly.

486
00:36:59,417 --> 00:37:03,251
And you put in
this big window.

487
00:37:03,354 --> 00:37:05,948
What a beautiful view
of the pond.

488
00:37:06,057 --> 00:37:08,082
- Why, you can see for miles!
- Mm-hmm.

489
00:37:08,192 --> 00:37:11,889
- The sun comes up right over that hill.
- Oh!

490
00:37:11,996 --> 00:37:15,397
- Do you like it?
- Why, it's unbelievable.

491
00:37:15,499 --> 00:37:18,491
Let's take your boots off, huh?

492
00:37:20,338 --> 00:37:24,502
Of course, there's a lot of work to
be done yet, but it'll be worth it.

493
00:37:26,043 --> 00:37:30,673
- Your feet are cold.
- I know. They're frozen.

494
00:37:33,451 --> 00:37:37,615
- The teapot. You found all the pieces.
- Mm-hmm.

495
00:37:37,722 --> 00:37:39,917
It took days and days.
[Chuckles]

496
00:37:44,562 --> 00:37:48,328
These stairs are
moving to the loft.

497
00:37:48,432 --> 00:37:50,992
I'll add the bedroom up there.

498
00:37:51,102 --> 00:37:54,594
The old millstone
I'm trying to make into a table.

499
00:37:59,577 --> 00:38:03,513
You know why i've started
to fix the place?

500
00:38:03,614 --> 00:38:07,175
I didn't want to say anything until
I knew I could make it livable...

501
00:38:07,285 --> 00:38:09,617
for us.

502
00:38:10,788 --> 00:38:14,224
Do you understand
What I'm saying, Cary?

503
00:38:14,325 --> 00:38:16,657
Yes.

504
00:38:16,761 --> 00:38:19,491
I'm asking you to marry me.

505
00:38:21,232 --> 00:38:24,224
I love you, Cary.

506
00:38:35,246 --> 00:38:39,148
L... I just hadn't
thought about marriage.

507
00:38:39,250 --> 00:38:42,151
Why do you think
i've been seeing you?

508
00:38:42,253 --> 00:38:44,619
I didn't think.

509
00:38:44,722 --> 00:38:48,419
- Can't you see it's impossible?
- No.

510
00:38:48,526 --> 00:38:51,120
This is the only thing
that matters.

511
00:38:54,265 --> 00:38:57,098
No. There are
other things that matter.

512
00:38:57,201 --> 00:39:01,137
The children... How could I ask them
to give up their home?

513
00:39:01,238 --> 00:39:04,298
Home is where you are, Cary.

514
00:39:04,408 --> 00:39:07,809
But the kind of life you lead,
l... I don't know that life.

515
00:39:07,912 --> 00:39:09,812
How could I make sure
it would work out?

516
00:39:09,914 --> 00:39:12,906
You can't, Cary.
You can't!

517
00:39:13,017 --> 00:39:16,976
Don't you see I'd be turning my back
on everything I've ever known?

518
00:39:17,088 --> 00:39:21,582
- Isn't it enough we love each other?
- No, cary.

519
00:39:21,692 --> 00:39:26,561
It isn't.
It isn't enough for either of us.

520
00:39:26,664 --> 00:39:31,567
You're running away from something
important because you're afraid.

521
00:39:31,669 --> 00:39:33,637
- Afraid?
- Mm-hmm.

522
00:39:33,738 --> 00:39:37,697
- Of what?
- Many things.

523
00:39:40,811 --> 00:39:44,474
Perhaps you're right.

524
00:39:44,582 --> 00:39:47,745
It's absurd
to think of marriage.

525
00:39:47,852 --> 00:39:50,821
- It's out of the question.
- Cary!

526
00:40:25,456 --> 00:40:28,653
The hours
you've spent mending it.

527
00:40:29,760 --> 00:40:31,694
Doesn't matter.

528
00:40:45,676 --> 00:40:47,576
Cary.

529
00:40:49,747 --> 00:40:52,716
Don't forget your boots.

530
00:40:58,622 --> 00:41:02,581
I'll help you.
You mustn't catch cold.

531
00:41:09,567 --> 00:41:13,196
Darling, don't cry.

532
00:41:14,905 --> 00:41:18,136
Oh, Ron,
I love you so much.

533
00:41:40,431 --> 00:41:42,729
What are you
thinking about?

534
00:41:44,735 --> 00:41:47,260
That I love you.

535
00:41:53,677 --> 00:41:55,941
It won't be easy.

536
00:41:57,047 --> 00:42:00,039
There will be
a lot of things that...

537
00:42:02,653 --> 00:42:05,486
You'll have to help me.

538
00:42:05,589 --> 00:42:08,558
I'll help all I can.

539
00:42:27,378 --> 00:42:31,041
- It's getting late.
- Mm-hmm.

540
00:42:31,148 --> 00:42:33,742
Does it matter?

541
00:42:35,953 --> 00:42:38,012
I'll take you home.

542
00:42:50,768 --> 00:42:54,067
[Man] I sent the boy up
with the roast twice on saturday.

543
00:42:54,171 --> 00:42:56,071
I kept phoning
up till 9:00 in the evening.

544
00:42:56,173 --> 00:42:58,266
I'm sorry,
but I completely forget.

545
00:42:58,375 --> 00:43:02,175
- Hello, Mrs. Plash.
- Hello. I was just thinking about you.

546
00:43:02,279 --> 00:43:04,474
- Pleasantly, I hope.
- Of course.

547
00:43:04,582 --> 00:43:07,779
I was telling Mrs. Scott
I couldn't figure out where she was.

548
00:43:07,885 --> 00:43:10,479
- I even phoned the club.
- Oh?

549
00:43:10,588 --> 00:43:14,684
The children weren't coming up so
I decided to go away for the weekend.

550
00:43:14,792 --> 00:43:17,761
- I'll take my roast now.
- Glad you had a chance to get away.

551
00:43:17,861 --> 00:43:20,830
- Where did you go, darling?
- Upstate.

552
00:43:20,931 --> 00:43:23,593
Good-bye.
Good-bye, Mona.

553
00:43:37,648 --> 00:43:41,448
It's comforting to know
she's not lonely, Mr. Gow.

554
00:43:44,188 --> 00:43:48,352
Mona Plash is such a gossip.

555
00:43:48,459 --> 00:43:51,292
It'll be all over town
by tomorrow, I'm afraid.

556
00:43:51,395 --> 00:43:55,764
I hate to have the children learn
about us before I tell them.

557
00:43:55,866 --> 00:43:58,494
Then you'd better tell them.

558
00:43:58,602 --> 00:44:01,196
It should be so simple.

559
00:44:01,305 --> 00:44:05,105
Two people who are in love
with each other, want to be married.

560
00:44:05,209 --> 00:44:07,143
Why is it so difficult
all of a sudden?

561
00:44:07,244 --> 00:44:10,873
It isn't,
if you're not afraid.

562
00:44:10,981 --> 00:44:14,439
That's what Mick
learned from you, isn't it?

563
00:44:14,551 --> 00:44:18,612
No. You can't learn that
from anybody.

564
00:44:20,424 --> 00:44:25,623
Mick discovered for himself that
he had to make his own decisions,

565
00:44:25,729 --> 00:44:29,062
that he had to be a man.

566
00:44:29,166 --> 00:44:32,101
And you want me to be a man.

567
00:44:32,202 --> 00:44:34,966
Only in that one way.

568
00:44:39,243 --> 00:44:42,303
Mona certainly didn't
waste any time, did she?

569
00:44:42,413 --> 00:44:44,779
I suppose the whole town's
talking about it.

570
00:44:44,882 --> 00:44:48,010
Well, she phoned me.
That's why I rushed over.

571
00:44:48,118 --> 00:44:51,178
Of course,
I didn't believe a word.

572
00:44:51,288 --> 00:44:53,950
You should.

573
00:44:54,058 --> 00:44:58,586
You can't be serious.
Your gardener?

574
00:44:58,696 --> 00:45:01,062
He isn't my gardener.

575
00:45:01,165 --> 00:45:04,066
He did work on the trees.
You met him.

576
00:45:04,168 --> 00:45:07,467
And even if he was,
I'm in love with him.

577
00:45:07,571 --> 00:45:10,597
And I'm going to marry him.

578
00:45:14,545 --> 00:45:18,174
Well, all right,
maybe I'm a snob.

579
00:45:18,282 --> 00:45:21,217
But it isn't just a question
of whether he's a gardener.

580
00:45:21,318 --> 00:45:23,252
The talk won't stop at that.

581
00:45:23,353 --> 00:45:26,789
They'll say he's
younger than you are.

582
00:45:26,890 --> 00:45:29,688
- And the fact that you're a widow.
- What does that got to do with it?

583
00:45:29,793 --> 00:45:33,160
- With money.
- Ron isn't interested in my money.

584
00:45:33,263 --> 00:45:36,562
And that he worked at your place
while Martin was still alive.

585
00:45:36,667 --> 00:45:40,933
People will say that all this started
before your husband died.

586
00:45:41,038 --> 00:45:44,974
- But that's not true. You...
- I don't!

587
00:45:45,075 --> 00:45:48,670
But Mona? Ha!
Mona will have a field day.

588
00:45:48,779 --> 00:45:52,772
Before she gets through,
the whole town will believe it.

589
00:45:52,883 --> 00:45:55,852
You know, Cary, as well as I do
that situations like this...

590
00:45:55,953 --> 00:46:00,322
bring out the hateful side
of human nature.

591
00:46:00,424 --> 00:46:03,757
Remember you have
Ned and Kay to think about.

592
00:46:03,861 --> 00:46:06,887
At their age,
what people say matters terribly.

593
00:46:06,997 --> 00:46:10,626
Have you stopped to think
what all these rumors will do to them?

594
00:46:10,734 --> 00:46:15,068
You're asking me to give up Ron because
of something in people that's mean?

595
00:46:15,172 --> 00:46:17,834
- I didn't say that.
- Do you think it would be good...

596
00:46:17,941 --> 00:46:22,742
if I were to let myself be
beaten by such hatefulness?

597
00:46:23,847 --> 00:46:26,475
Well, I'm not gonna do it.

598
00:46:26,583 --> 00:46:29,814
Let them say what they want to.

599
00:46:29,920 --> 00:46:33,287
And that goes for you too, Sara.

600
00:46:35,425 --> 00:46:39,885
I must say, Cary,
you've got stubbornness.

601
00:46:41,031 --> 00:46:43,864
And courage.

602
00:46:45,369 --> 00:46:48,736
If you want to throw me out,
I won't blame you.

603
00:46:48,839 --> 00:46:51,808
I apologize.
At least I can do that much.

604
00:46:51,909 --> 00:46:55,470
You don't have
to apologize, Sara, just...

605
00:46:55,579 --> 00:46:57,638
just go on being my friend.

606
00:46:57,748 --> 00:47:00,239
I'd be a fool not to do that.

607
00:47:00,350 --> 00:47:03,979
I've got to give a cocktail party
this weekend for that moron Jo-Ann.

608
00:47:04,087 --> 00:47:06,612
She bagged Tom Allenby.

609
00:47:06,723 --> 00:47:11,387
You bring Ron.
Maybe if people see him,

610
00:47:11,495 --> 00:47:15,625
maybe if they get to know him,
they'll accept him.

611
00:47:19,069 --> 00:47:22,004
Well, I'll call him.

612
00:47:33,016 --> 00:47:35,382
Good evening, Mrs. Plash.

613
00:47:35,485 --> 00:47:38,010
- Hello, ned. You home for the weekend?
- Yes, I am.

614
00:47:38,121 --> 00:47:41,113
Just wait until you see your mother.
She's never looked so radiant.

615
00:47:41,225 --> 00:47:44,285
- I wish I knew her secret.
- Thank you, Mrs. Plash.

616
00:47:44,394 --> 00:47:46,362
- Lf you'll excuse me, I've got to hurry.
- Mm-hmm.

617
00:47:46,463 --> 00:47:48,988
Yoo-hoo, Mildred!
How was New York?

618
00:47:54,571 --> 00:47:56,903
Mother?

619
00:48:01,979 --> 00:48:04,038
I'm home!
Where are ya?

620
00:48:04,147 --> 00:48:07,605
I'm in the basement, dear.
I'll be up in a minute.

621
00:48:14,491 --> 00:48:16,982
- Ned?
- Yeah.

622
00:48:17,094 --> 00:48:19,961
- How are you, dear?
- What were you doing in the cellar?

623
00:48:20,063 --> 00:48:22,224
I was putting some things
away in the storage closet.

624
00:48:22,332 --> 00:48:24,391
Everything was getting
so cluttered.

625
00:48:24,501 --> 00:48:27,402
Where's Kay? She and Freddie
were supposed to drive up together.

626
00:48:27,504 --> 00:48:29,836
She's upstairs.
We've been waiting for you.

627
00:48:29,940 --> 00:48:32,408
Why all the mystery when
you phoned? Who's coming?

628
00:48:37,681 --> 00:48:41,981
Oh, mother, I hope you don't mind
my borrowing your manicure set.

629
00:48:42,085 --> 00:48:44,849
Which is better?
Crimson snow or traffic light?

630
00:48:44,955 --> 00:48:48,049
[Ned] Oh, dig you. Since
when have you joined the female ranks?

631
00:48:48,158 --> 00:48:50,183
- All right!
- Now, Kay, Ned.

632
00:48:50,294 --> 00:48:55,231
I want to discuss something with you
that concerns you as much as me.

633
00:48:55,332 --> 00:48:57,857
You're going to get married.

634
00:48:59,836 --> 00:49:03,795
Why, yes.
How did you know?

635
00:49:03,907 --> 00:49:06,307
Oh, it had to happen.

636
00:49:06,410 --> 00:49:08,344
Anyone as attractive as you.

637
00:49:08,445 --> 00:49:11,812
Besides, you know what I think
of widows being walled up alive.

638
00:49:11,915 --> 00:49:14,406
Egyptian fashion.

639
00:49:14,518 --> 00:49:16,679
I knew you felt that way in theory.

640
00:49:16,787 --> 00:49:18,880
Theory and action should be one.

641
00:49:18,989 --> 00:49:21,321
Don't worry, Mother.
We're all for it.

642
00:49:21,425 --> 00:49:23,393
Oh, darlings.

643
00:49:23,493 --> 00:49:25,518
Hey, save that for Harvey.

644
00:49:26,630 --> 00:49:29,098
Harvey?

645
00:49:29,199 --> 00:49:34,364
Well, it isn't Harvey.
It... It's Ron Kirby.

646
00:49:35,505 --> 00:49:38,201
You know him.
At least you've met him.

647
00:49:38,308 --> 00:49:40,833
The only Kirby I know
is old Kirby the gardener.

648
00:49:40,944 --> 00:49:46,075
- Last I heard, he was dead.
- Ron is his son.

649
00:49:46,183 --> 00:49:48,583
Mother, is this a joke or something?

650
00:49:48,685 --> 00:49:51,313
- No, it isn't a joke, Ned.
- But, Mother, you can't...

651
00:49:51,421 --> 00:49:54,788
There's no point in approaching this
emotionally. Let's try to be objective.

652
00:49:54,891 --> 00:49:56,791
This isn't one of your
case histories. This is us!

653
00:49:56,893 --> 00:50:01,830
Just the same. Now, Mother, have you
introduced him to any of your friends?

654
00:50:01,932 --> 00:50:03,866
[Ned]
Yeah, what does Sara think?

655
00:50:03,967 --> 00:50:07,459
Well, Sara's invited us
to a cocktail party tonight.

656
00:50:07,571 --> 00:50:11,564
I wanted you to know him first,
so I asked Ron to come early...

657
00:50:11,675 --> 00:50:13,609
for a drink,
one of your special martinis.

658
00:50:13,710 --> 00:50:15,940
This is no time for martinis.

659
00:50:16,046 --> 00:50:18,879
Mother, why did you keep
this whole affair such a secret?

660
00:50:18,982 --> 00:50:21,644
Because subconsciously
you were afraid he wouldn't fit in?

661
00:50:21,752 --> 00:50:25,244
Why, Ron has no intentions
of fitting in, Kay.

662
00:50:25,355 --> 00:50:27,550
He's quite content
with his life the way it is.

663
00:50:27,657 --> 00:50:31,252
- Mother, the whole thing is impossible.
- You don't know him.

664
00:50:31,361 --> 00:50:33,795
- We know the type.
- And we know you, Mother.

665
00:50:33,897 --> 00:50:38,391
- [Doorbell Ringing]
- Suppose that's him now.

666
00:50:38,502 --> 00:50:41,835
You must realize how
important this is to me.

667
00:50:41,938 --> 00:50:46,841
I'm relying on both of you
to be fair and... give Ron a chance.

668
00:50:46,943 --> 00:50:51,209
All right.
I'll make the martinis.

669
00:51:00,090 --> 00:51:02,024
Won't you come in, Ron?

670
00:51:04,594 --> 00:51:08,030
- You know Ned and Kay?
- Yes, of course. Hello.

671
00:51:08,131 --> 00:51:11,100
- It's nice to see you again.
- Thank you.

672
00:51:11,201 --> 00:51:13,863
Shall we go into the living room?

673
00:51:16,206 --> 00:51:19,733
Kay, as I told you, Ron,
is doing social work in New York.

674
00:51:19,843 --> 00:51:25,440
- You like it, I understand.
- You learn to deal with all sorts.

675
00:51:25,549 --> 00:51:29,110
- NNed, you make a very good martini.
- Not too strong for you?

676
00:51:29,219 --> 00:51:31,687
- You still have the nursery, Mr. Kirby?
- Oh, yes.

677
00:51:31,788 --> 00:51:34,450
He's going in more
for tree farming now.

678
00:51:34,558 --> 00:51:37,959
- Is there any money in growing trees?
- There can be.

679
00:51:38,061 --> 00:51:40,962
The only thing I know about trees
is they make good logs.

680
00:51:41,064 --> 00:51:43,999
- Now's your chance to learn.
- Mother?

681
00:51:44,101 --> 00:51:48,765
- What happened to dad's trophy?
- Why, nothing happened to it.

682
00:51:50,373 --> 00:51:53,342
Is the trophy part of the clutter
you were putting away?

683
00:51:53,443 --> 00:51:55,343
Ned.

684
00:51:57,814 --> 00:52:03,150
I suppose from now on,
there'll be lots of changes around here.

685
00:52:03,253 --> 00:52:08,555
Ned, if you mean because of my marriage
to your mother, you needn't worry.

686
00:52:08,658 --> 00:52:13,027
I have no intention of living here.
We'll be leading quite a different life.

687
00:52:13,130 --> 00:52:15,894
But this has been the family house
for I don't know how long.

688
00:52:15,999 --> 00:52:17,899
This is the place
we were born!

689
00:52:18,001 --> 00:52:21,903
Ned, I wish you'd treat this matter
in a more detached fashion.

690
00:52:22,005 --> 00:52:25,702
You don't know Mother as we know her.
She's really much more conventional...

691
00:52:25,809 --> 00:52:27,709
than you seem to think she is.

692
00:52:27,811 --> 00:52:31,474
She has the innate desire for group
approval, which most women have.

693
00:52:31,581 --> 00:52:34,573
Never mind the $10 words.

694
00:52:34,684 --> 00:52:37,983
And where, if I may ask,
do you expect our mother...

695
00:52:38,088 --> 00:52:40,886
and, I suppose, us too to live?

696
00:52:40,991 --> 00:52:43,084
- My place.
- In a greenhouse?

697
00:52:43,193 --> 00:52:47,289
Oh, no, no.
He's going to remodel the old mill.

698
00:52:47,397 --> 00:52:51,299
Mother, if you'll excuse me, I'm going
to a lecture. I'd better get ready.

699
00:52:51,401 --> 00:52:53,369
Good-bye, Mr. Kirby.

700
00:52:53,470 --> 00:52:56,735
Mother, I've got some
studying to catch up on.

701
00:53:00,277 --> 00:53:03,735
What happened? I've never
seen them act like that before.

702
00:53:03,847 --> 00:53:07,146
It's natural, Cary.
I'm not like their father.

703
00:53:07,250 --> 00:53:09,184
What does that
got to do with it?

704
00:53:09,286 --> 00:53:13,382
It would be different if you were
marrying the same kind of man.

705
00:53:13,490 --> 00:53:17,290
Successful businessman,
pillar of the community.

706
00:53:17,394 --> 00:53:19,294
I can understand it.

707
00:53:20,397 --> 00:53:22,365
Perhaps you're right.

708
00:53:23,733 --> 00:53:27,601
But once I make them see that...
Shall we get started?

709
00:53:27,704 --> 00:53:30,298
Cary, do we really have to go?

710
00:53:32,175 --> 00:53:36,874
Well, Sara said that...
And anyway, I want to show you off.

711
00:53:50,727 --> 00:53:53,719
- We can take my car.
- Mine's right here.

712
00:53:56,233 --> 00:53:59,896
- Does it matter that much?
- It shouldn't.

713
00:54:02,339 --> 00:54:05,672
Jim, get me another one, will you?
I don't want to miss the arrival.

714
00:54:05,775 --> 00:54:09,006
- How about you, Mrs. Taylor?
- Well, I really shouldn't, but...

715
00:54:10,380 --> 00:54:12,314
Excuse me.

716
00:54:12,415 --> 00:54:14,406
If you see cary before I do,
let me know.

717
00:54:14,517 --> 00:54:16,542
It'll be easier for her
if I took them around.

718
00:54:16,653 --> 00:54:19,520
- Count on it, Sara. Got a light?
- I may need to.

719
00:54:19,623 --> 00:54:21,818
Hold my drink, dear.
A gardener?

720
00:54:21,925 --> 00:54:24,189
Why doesn't he find himself
a decent money-making vocation?

721
00:54:24,294 --> 00:54:26,990
You think material success is the only
end worthy of pursuit of man?

722
00:54:27,097 --> 00:54:29,998
- What's wrong with money?
- You have to have it to have contempt.

723
00:54:30,100 --> 00:54:32,125
Excuse me.

724
00:54:32,235 --> 00:54:36,672
Thank you. Do you really think
she'll have the nerve to come?

725
00:54:36,773 --> 00:54:39,241
- Oh, there they are now!
- They're here!

726
00:54:50,020 --> 00:54:53,353
- Just look at that car.
- Just look at that man.

727
00:54:53,456 --> 00:54:55,356
Daughter!

728
00:54:55,458 --> 00:54:57,449
It's always the quiet ones,
isn't it?

729
00:54:57,560 --> 00:54:59,528
But she's certainly the last person
you'd expect to...

730
00:54:59,629 --> 00:55:02,928
Always pretending
to be so prim and proper.

731
00:55:03,033 --> 00:55:05,433
Why, Howard,
did she turn you down?

732
00:55:05,535 --> 00:55:08,333
I'm so glad you could come.
I'm Cary's best friend.

733
00:55:08,438 --> 00:55:10,463
- I'd like to be your friend too.
- Thank you.

734
00:55:10,573 --> 00:55:13,201
Come on, darling. George.

735
00:55:13,310 --> 00:55:16,837
- Cary, my favorite woman.
- George, I want you to know Ron Kirby.

736
00:55:16,946 --> 00:55:19,972
- Used to know your father. Fine man.
- Thank you.

737
00:55:20,083 --> 00:55:24,019
Shall we say hello to Romeo
and his Juliet? Come on, darling.

738
00:55:24,120 --> 00:55:26,554
So that's Cary's nature boy.

739
00:55:26,656 --> 00:55:29,216
- You know the doctor, Dan.
- Hello, Cary.

740
00:55:29,326 --> 00:55:31,954
You know Miss Frisbee,
Mr. Allenby. Mr. Kirby.

741
00:55:32,062 --> 00:55:34,223
- How do you do?
- How do you do?

742
00:55:34,331 --> 00:55:36,299
This was kind of
supposed to be my party,

743
00:55:36,399 --> 00:55:39,129
but looks like Mrs. Scott's
getting the attention.

744
00:55:39,235 --> 00:55:43,194
I guess it is more unusual
when someone your age gets married.

745
00:55:43,306 --> 00:55:46,275
But I think your friend's
awfully lucky.

746
00:55:46,376 --> 00:55:49,868
You see, no one in my family's
had a dime since the civil war.

747
00:55:49,979 --> 00:55:54,507
So, Tom won't get anything
but poor little me.

748
00:55:54,617 --> 00:55:58,883
- Don't bother, Cary...
- My dear. What's this i hear about...

749
00:55:58,988 --> 00:56:02,719
Oh. Haven't I seen you
somewhere before?

750
00:56:02,826 --> 00:56:05,624
Well, Mrs. Humphrey,
probably in your garden.

751
00:56:05,729 --> 00:56:08,926
I've been pruning your trees
for the last three years.

752
00:56:09,032 --> 00:56:12,160
Oh, yes, of course.

753
00:56:12,268 --> 00:56:16,204
- Ah, sara, I really must be going.
- I'll be right back.

754
00:56:16,306 --> 00:56:19,571
Come into the bar. You've earned
yourself a good strong drink.

755
00:56:19,676 --> 00:56:22,270
- Go ahead, Ron.
- I'll be right back.

756
00:56:22,379 --> 00:56:24,506
All right.

757
00:56:24,614 --> 00:56:26,582
- Howard.
- Hi.

758
00:56:26,683 --> 00:56:28,742
How are you?

759
00:56:30,053 --> 00:56:33,614
- Mona, Mark.
- Oh, my dear, he's fascinating.

760
00:56:33,723 --> 00:56:36,954
And that tan!
I suppose from working outdoors.

761
00:56:37,060 --> 00:56:39,858
Of course, i'm sure
he's handy indoors too.

762
00:56:43,266 --> 00:56:45,530
Mona's sure got your number, Cary.

763
00:56:47,704 --> 00:56:50,036
So have I.

764
00:56:50,140 --> 00:56:52,631
Well, excuse me, Howard.

765
00:57:00,550 --> 00:57:04,452
Guess you played me for a prize sucker
that night at the club, huh?

766
00:57:04,554 --> 00:57:08,513
Goin' into that perfect lady routine.
Makin' me apologize.

767
00:57:08,625 --> 00:57:10,559
If I'd known then
what I know now,

768
00:57:10,660 --> 00:57:13,288
- would have had a different ending.
- Oh, Howard.

769
00:57:13,396 --> 00:57:16,991
Never too late, huh, Cary?
Line forms to the right.

770
00:57:17,100 --> 00:57:19,694
- Howard, you're drunk!
- Why, Cary!

771
00:57:19,803 --> 00:57:21,737
Isn't one man
enough for you?

772
00:57:21,838 --> 00:57:24,807
Maybe you'd better stay
right where you are.

773
00:57:24,908 --> 00:57:26,569
[Sara]
What is it, Cary?

774
00:57:26,676 --> 00:57:29,577
- I never would have believed it.
[Sara] Believed what?

775
00:57:29,679 --> 00:57:32,614
[Mona] That Howard was the earthy
type. You seem to attract that, Cary.

776
00:57:32,715 --> 00:57:34,615
- Shall we go?
- Yes.

777
00:57:36,119 --> 00:57:38,178
- Excuse us.
- Oh, george!

778
00:57:38,288 --> 00:57:40,119
Why, that man was
positively murderous.

779
00:57:40,223 --> 00:57:42,453
- Did you see that, Fred?
- What's the commotion?

780
00:57:42,559 --> 00:57:44,652
He might have
killed poor Howard.

781
00:57:44,761 --> 00:57:46,956
- And in Sara's lovely house too!
- Well!

782
00:58:02,345 --> 00:58:04,870
Nothing's important except us.

783
00:58:04,981 --> 00:58:07,415
Will you remember that?

784
00:58:07,517 --> 00:58:09,508
Yes.

785
00:58:09,619 --> 00:58:12,281
- I'll take you to the door.
- No, Ron.

786
00:58:12,388 --> 00:58:15,846
Thank you, but... good night.

787
00:58:15,959 --> 00:58:17,950
Good night.

788
00:58:29,339 --> 00:58:31,603
Ned, you're still up?

789
00:58:34,043 --> 00:58:39,481
Don't forget to put the screen around
the fireplace before you come up.

790
00:58:39,582 --> 00:58:41,846
Mom...

791
00:58:41,951 --> 00:58:45,853
I've got a few things
to say to you, Mother.

792
00:58:45,955 --> 00:58:47,855
All right, Ned.

793
00:58:47,957 --> 00:58:52,656
I just want to tell you, meeting him
hasn't changed my mind one darn bit.

794
00:58:52,762 --> 00:58:54,821
We did what you asked.

795
00:58:54,931 --> 00:58:58,958
I asked you to give Ron a fair chance.
I don't think you did.

796
00:58:59,068 --> 00:59:01,832
Just because we didn't agree
with your choice?

797
00:59:01,938 --> 00:59:06,136
Listen, Mother, somebody in this
family's gotta think straight.

798
00:59:06,242 --> 00:59:08,267
And you don't think I can?

799
00:59:08,378 --> 00:59:11,779
I think all you see is
a good-looking set of muscles.

800
00:59:11,881 --> 00:59:13,872
Why, Ned!

801
00:59:13,983 --> 00:59:18,010
That's the way it looks,
doesn't it?

802
00:59:18,121 --> 00:59:22,581
You're planning to give up a home that's
been in the family for I don't know...

803
00:59:22,692 --> 00:59:25,559
There's a certain tradition.

804
00:59:25,662 --> 00:59:28,495
Aand for what?

805
00:59:28,598 --> 00:59:31,795
Don't you realize
what people are gonna say?

806
00:59:31,901 --> 00:59:35,962
Haven't you any sense
of obligation to father's memory?

807
00:59:36,072 --> 00:59:38,404
What does that
got to do with it?

808
00:59:38,508 --> 00:59:42,877
How can you think of marrying Kirby
when you've been Father's wife?

809
00:59:42,979 --> 00:59:46,437
- It's against everything.
- Nonsense, Ned.

810
00:59:48,217 --> 00:59:53,655
Mother... are you really
intending to go through with this?

811
00:59:57,260 --> 00:59:59,387
Yes, I am.

812
01:00:00,563 --> 01:00:04,055
Well, don't expect me
to come visit ya.

813
01:00:04,167 --> 01:00:08,069
How could I bring my friends?
I'd be ashamed.

814
01:00:11,641 --> 01:00:13,541
Ned!

815
01:00:18,281 --> 01:00:22,240
Ned, we mustn't let this
come between us.

816
01:00:22,352 --> 01:00:27,153
If you mean Kirby,
he already has!

817
01:00:28,257 --> 01:00:30,191
[Door Slamming]

818
01:00:39,969 --> 01:00:43,700
And then Ned
on top of everything else.

819
01:00:43,806 --> 01:00:47,003
No, I haven't heard a word.
I've got a call in for him.

820
01:00:47,110 --> 01:00:49,977
Well, Kay stayed over.

821
01:00:51,280 --> 01:00:54,215
- I didn't sleep a wink either.
- [Door Closing]

822
01:00:54,317 --> 01:00:56,785
Do you really think
the talk will die down?

823
01:00:56,886 --> 01:00:59,354
Kay?

824
01:00:59,455 --> 01:01:02,652
Sara, I'll have to call you back later.
All right.

825
01:01:08,731 --> 01:01:11,063
- Kay, darling, what is it?

826
01:01:11,167 --> 01:01:14,603
What's the matter?
Well, tell me.

827
01:01:14,704 --> 01:01:16,968
Nothing. It...

828
01:01:17,073 --> 01:01:20,600
It's about me, isn't it?

829
01:01:23,413 --> 01:01:27,474
Freddie and I
were at the library.

830
01:01:27,583 --> 01:01:30,017
One of the kids
made a crack about you.

831
01:01:30,119 --> 01:01:32,610
What did they say?

832
01:01:32,722 --> 01:01:36,351
That you and Mr. Kirby were...
even before Daddy...

833
01:01:36,459 --> 01:01:38,427
Now, you stop that, Kay.
You know that's a lie.

834
01:01:38,528 --> 01:01:41,429
Of course I do,
and I told them so!

835
01:01:41,531 --> 01:01:44,728
They went on and on
and I got mad and...

836
01:01:44,834 --> 01:01:49,100
We were asked to leave.

837
01:01:49,205 --> 01:01:52,606
Oh, darling.

838
01:01:54,210 --> 01:01:57,873
And on the way home
Freddie and I had a fight.

839
01:01:57,980 --> 01:02:00,676
I told him that i didn't care
what people said.

840
01:02:00,783 --> 01:02:05,550
But, Mama, I do care!
I care terribly!

841
01:02:06,923 --> 01:02:12,020
Oh, Kay, l... I don't know what to do.

842
01:02:12,128 --> 01:02:15,359
I can't bear to see
you and ned so unhappy.

843
01:02:15,465 --> 01:02:19,663
But, you see, Kay, I love Ron.

844
01:02:19,769 --> 01:02:23,000
You love him so much
you're willing to ruin all our lives?

845
01:02:23,106 --> 01:02:27,543
- You can't really think that.
- What else can I think?

846
01:02:28,811 --> 01:02:32,269
But, Kay, you've talked
so much about people...

847
01:02:32,381 --> 01:02:34,406
and why they do
the things they do.

848
01:02:34,517 --> 01:02:37,543
- You say you understand.
- But I don't!

849
01:02:37,653 --> 01:02:40,520
I don't! I thought I did.

850
01:02:40,623 --> 01:02:43,786
I don't understand anything.

851
01:03:26,869 --> 01:03:28,769
Cary?

852
01:03:30,506 --> 01:03:34,806
- Oh, Ron, l...
- What's the matter?

853
01:03:35,912 --> 01:03:39,211
Well, Ned's left home and l...

854
01:03:39,315 --> 01:03:43,149
I left Kay in tears. Some of her
friends have been dreadful to her.

855
01:03:43,252 --> 01:03:45,186
Because of me?

856
01:03:47,657 --> 01:03:52,151
Ron, we're gonna have
to wait to get married.

857
01:03:52,261 --> 01:03:55,162
- Why?
- Well...

858
01:03:55,264 --> 01:03:58,290
To give the children
a chance to get used to the idea.

859
01:03:58,401 --> 01:04:01,097
They'll feel differently
when they know you better.

860
01:04:01,204 --> 01:04:04,105
- You don't want to marry me?
- I'm not saying that.

861
01:04:04,207 --> 01:04:08,109
I'm asking you to be patient.
It's only a question of time.

862
01:04:08,211 --> 01:04:11,374
Only of time?

863
01:04:11,480 --> 01:04:15,678
Right now everybody's talking about us.
We're a local sensation.

864
01:04:15,785 --> 01:04:19,915
Like Sara said, if the people get used
to seeing us together,

865
01:04:20,022 --> 01:04:23,253
then maybe
they'll accept us.

866
01:04:23,359 --> 01:04:28,126
You mean, we'll be invited
to all the cocktail parties.

867
01:04:28,231 --> 01:04:32,600
And, of course, Sara will see to it
I get into the country club.

868
01:04:32,702 --> 01:04:36,229
Dear Howard and I will
shake hands and forget.

869
01:04:36,339 --> 01:04:39,035
- And Mona won't be malicious.
- That isn't what I mean.

870
01:04:39,141 --> 01:04:41,041
And ned and kay
won't mind so much...

871
01:04:41,143 --> 01:04:43,270
because we'll be living
just as you always have.

872
01:04:43,379 --> 01:04:47,941
- Probably in your house.
- What's wrong with that?

873
01:04:48,050 --> 01:04:51,451
It's only for a little while.
It would make things so much easier.

874
01:04:51,554 --> 01:04:53,715
It wouldn't change you.
You couldn't be changed.

875
01:04:53,823 --> 01:04:56,348
Yes, I could.

876
01:04:56,459 --> 01:05:00,623
I'm learning right now how easy
it would be to let myself be changed.

877
01:05:00,730 --> 01:05:03,528
- By whom?
- By you.

878
01:05:04,634 --> 01:05:07,797
I'm sorry, Cary.
But it wouldn't work.

879
01:05:07,904 --> 01:05:11,203
I can't live that way.
You knew that from the beginning.

880
01:05:11,307 --> 01:05:15,107
But I can't ruin
my children's lives.

881
01:05:15,211 --> 01:05:17,304
I have a responsibility to them.

882
01:05:17,413 --> 01:05:20,041
Are you sure it's just that?

883
01:05:22,451 --> 01:05:25,318
Well, what do you mean?

884
01:05:25,421 --> 01:05:28,982
- You don't think I care what people say.
- Yes, I do.

885
01:05:29,091 --> 01:05:31,924
You're not even trying
to understand.

886
01:05:32,028 --> 01:05:35,862
- How can you say you love me...
- God knows I love you.

887
01:05:35,965 --> 01:05:39,901
But I won't let Ned nor Kay
nor anyone else run our lives.

888
01:05:40,002 --> 01:05:42,971
Don't you see we could never
be happy if we did?

889
01:05:43,072 --> 01:05:46,132
I can see that you don't want to listen
to anybody's ideas but your own.

890
01:05:46,242 --> 01:05:49,177
I can see that you're trying to make
me choose between you and the children!

891
01:05:49,278 --> 01:05:53,374
No, Cary, you're the one
that made it a question of choosing.

892
01:05:53,482 --> 01:05:55,416
So you're the one
that'll have to choose.

893
01:05:59,121 --> 01:06:01,885
All right.

894
01:06:04,794 --> 01:06:06,819
It's all over.

895
01:06:13,536 --> 01:06:15,504
Cary?

896
01:06:46,535 --> 01:06:51,131
I admit, after meeting him,
he's a darn nice guy, but l...

897
01:06:53,309 --> 01:06:56,642
But I still say
you did the right thing.

898
01:06:59,615 --> 01:07:03,574
Oh... I suppose so.

899
01:07:03,686 --> 01:07:08,589
Everyone will welcome you back
to the fold. I'll see to that.

900
01:07:08,691 --> 01:07:11,524
I don't know what i'd do
without you, Sara.

901
01:07:11,627 --> 01:07:14,562
I know what you've been
going through.

902
01:07:14,663 --> 01:07:19,225
I know it hasn't been easy.
But at least you have the children.

903
01:07:19,335 --> 01:07:23,567
You don't have to fiill your life
with club work and parties.

904
01:07:23,672 --> 01:07:26,732
- Oh, Sara.

905
01:07:26,842 --> 01:07:29,606
That must be Ned.
I have a call in for him.

906
01:07:29,712 --> 01:07:32,681
- You've told Kay?
- Yes, she's very happy.

907
01:07:32,782 --> 01:07:34,682
- Hello?
- Mrs. Scott?

908
01:07:34,784 --> 01:07:36,684
- Yes.
- I have your party now.

909
01:07:36,786 --> 01:07:38,981
- [Ned] Mother, you called me?
- Yes, Ned, I did.

910
01:07:39,088 --> 01:07:44,151
I wanted to talk to you.
I, um... I've decided that...

911
01:07:44,260 --> 01:07:46,592
Well, I'm not going
to be married.

912
01:07:46,695 --> 01:07:49,493
- Oh, great.
- You will be up this weekend?

913
01:07:49,598 --> 01:07:52,863
You bet, Mom.
I got a class now, so good-bye, huh?

914
01:07:52,968 --> 01:07:56,529
- Well, Ned... Ned?

915
01:08:02,078 --> 01:08:05,536
Was he pleased?

916
01:08:07,049 --> 01:08:11,247
Yes, he...
He seemed to be.

917
01:08:20,496 --> 01:08:23,488
- Hello, dear!
- Bill! I thought you'd never get here.

918
01:08:23,599 --> 01:08:27,433
- What's for dinner?
- Good night. Say hello to the children.

919
01:08:27,536 --> 01:08:30,630
- Hello, Cary. Nice to see you.
- Hello, Doctor. Nice to see you.

920
01:08:30,739 --> 01:08:33,469
I've been meaning to call you
about a checkup.

921
01:08:33,576 --> 01:08:37,273
I don't think it's serious, but
I've been having miserable headaches.

922
01:08:37,379 --> 01:08:40,473
- Any time. Can I give you a lift?
- I'm waiting for the children.

923
01:08:40,583 --> 01:08:43,279
- Let me hear from you now.
- All right.

924
01:08:51,560 --> 01:08:53,460
Oh, Mrs. Scott.

925
01:08:53,562 --> 01:08:55,996
Seems the kids couldn't make it.

926
01:08:56,098 --> 01:09:00,057
Guess they're pretty busy
with the holidays coming on.

927
