- Hello, Mama! Merry Christmas!
- Merry Christmas!

969
01:12:18,967 --> 01:12:22,027
- Thought we'd never get here.
- I'm so happy to see you.

970
01:12:22,137 --> 01:12:25,004
- Oh, it looks gorgeous!
- Hey, look at all that loot!

971
01:12:25,107 --> 01:12:28,167
- Is that for me?
- Where's our present for you?

972
01:12:28,277 --> 01:12:30,370
Nothing's come.
But don't worry about it.

973
01:12:30,479 --> 01:12:33,380
- Just having the two of you is enough.
- I better phone.

974
01:12:33,482 --> 01:12:36,383
- Not here. It's a secret!

975
01:12:36,485 --> 01:12:38,783
- Don't open anything until I get back.
- All right.

976
01:12:38,887 --> 01:12:41,822
Mama!

977
01:12:41,924 --> 01:12:43,824
Look!

978
01:12:48,664 --> 01:12:50,632
Why, that's lovely, Kay.

979
01:12:50,733 --> 01:12:52,701
Freddie and I
are going to be married.

980
01:12:52,801 --> 01:12:56,328
In february,
after he graduates.

981
01:12:56,438 --> 01:12:58,497
Well, aren't you a little young?

982
01:12:58,607 --> 01:13:02,008
You were 17 when you got married.

983
01:13:05,614 --> 01:13:08,515
But... it's so soon.

984
01:13:08,617 --> 01:13:10,881
Soon?
Oh, it seems like forever.

985
01:13:10,986 --> 01:13:13,546
Oh, Mama!

986
01:13:13,655 --> 01:13:18,490
Remember the afternoon
that Freddie and I had the big fight?

987
01:13:18,594 --> 01:13:23,691
That's when we found out we loved
each other. Mama, he's so wonderful.

988
01:13:23,799 --> 01:13:27,064
Yes, I remember.

989
01:13:27,169 --> 01:13:31,936
That was the day you told me your life
would be ruined if I married Ron.

990
01:13:33,675 --> 01:13:38,237
I was being childish. You shouldn't
have let me get away with it.

991
01:13:38,347 --> 01:13:41,407
Of course, that was different.

992
01:13:41,517 --> 01:13:45,613
You didn't really love him,
did you?

993
01:13:45,721 --> 01:13:48,053
Mother!

994
01:13:48,157 --> 01:13:50,148
Your present's on the way.

995
01:13:50,259 --> 01:13:53,092
Hey, this is Christmas.
Let's enjoy it.

996
01:13:53,195 --> 01:13:56,392
After all, it'll probably
be the last one we spend in this house.

997
01:13:56,498 --> 01:13:58,398
What do you mean?

998
01:13:58,500 --> 01:14:02,766
Kay's getting married.
And if I'm not called up right away,

999
01:14:02,871 --> 01:14:05,465
I'm in line for the Walker Scholarship
which means a year in Paris.

1000
01:14:05,574 --> 01:14:08,737
After that, onto Iran
with the Dayton Company.

1001
01:14:08,844 --> 01:14:12,211
I didn't want to tell you till
I had it pretty well cinched.

1002
01:14:12,314 --> 01:14:14,214
Hey, Mother.

1003
01:14:14,316 --> 01:14:16,216
Thank you.

1004
01:14:18,220 --> 01:14:21,212
Yes, with Kay and I away,
I think we should sell the house.

1005
01:14:21,323 --> 01:14:23,917
The house?

1006
01:14:24,026 --> 01:14:26,187
It's too big for one person.
What with taxes...

1007
01:14:26,295 --> 01:14:28,593
There's your present now.

1008
01:14:34,403 --> 01:14:37,372
- [Door Opening]
- Mama?

1009
01:14:39,775 --> 01:14:42,972
- Mama!

1010
01:14:43,078 --> 01:14:48,710
Don't you see, Kay?
The whole thing's been so pointless.

1011
01:14:50,552 --> 01:14:53,453
Oh, mama, I'm...
I'm terribly sorry.

1012
01:14:53,555 --> 01:14:56,456
I didn't mean to hurt you.

1013
01:14:59,328 --> 01:15:04,231
Mama, it still isn't too late,
if he loves you.

1014
01:15:06,568 --> 01:15:10,800
- Please, Kay, it...
- Mother?

1015
01:15:10,906 --> 01:15:13,033
Merry Christmas!

1016
01:15:13,141 --> 01:15:17,237
Merry Christmas, Mrs. Scott,
and Happy New Year.

1017
01:15:17,346 --> 01:15:19,644
Kay and I couldn't afford
anything but a table model.

1018
01:15:19,748 --> 01:15:22,012
It's got a nice-sized screen
and it's easy to operate.

1019
01:15:22,117 --> 01:15:26,417
All you have to do is turn that dial and
you have all the company you want...

1020
01:15:26,522 --> 01:15:28,456
right there on the screen.

1021
01:15:28,557 --> 01:15:33,620
Drama, comedy, life's parade
at your fiingertips.

1022
01:15:48,410 --> 01:15:51,004
Fetch, go on!
Fetch, old boy!

1023
01:15:51,113 --> 01:15:54,640
Ha, ha!
Boy, are you slippin'.

1024
01:15:54,750 --> 01:15:58,049
Why don't you try
using shells in that gun?

1025
01:15:58,153 --> 01:16:00,178
- Doesn't seem to help.
- Ha, ha!

1026
01:16:00,289 --> 01:16:03,190
Can't shoot straight anymore,
I guess.

1027
01:16:03,292 --> 01:16:05,852
I don't seem to be good
for anything lately.

1028
01:16:05,961 --> 01:16:08,953
You haven't been good for anything
since you and Cary broke up.

1029
01:16:09,064 --> 01:16:12,363
- What's that got to do with it?
- Everything, and you know it.

1030
01:16:12,467 --> 01:16:14,731
You're not the same anymore.

1031
01:16:14,836 --> 01:16:16,736
You're no good to me,
yourself or anyone.

1032
01:16:16,838 --> 01:16:19,136
All right,
so what do I do about it?

1033
01:16:19,241 --> 01:16:21,869
- Call her up. Go see her. Apologize.
- Apologize for what?

1034
01:16:21,977 --> 01:16:24,810
I don't know for what.
For anything. Make up something.

1035
01:16:24,913 --> 01:16:26,813
- But do something.

1036
01:16:26,915 --> 01:16:31,352
That's a boy. Good boy.
Hey, nice, huh?

1037
01:16:31,453 --> 01:16:34,945
Look, Mick,
I told her that I love her.

1038
01:16:35,057 --> 01:16:38,686
I asked her to marry me. I can't force
her. She has to make up her own mind.

1039
01:16:38,794 --> 01:16:41,490
She doesn't want to make up her
own mind. No girl does.

1040
01:16:41,597 --> 01:16:44,088
She wants you
to make it up for her.

1041
01:16:44,199 --> 01:16:47,430
- Come on, let's go.
- No, I'll be along later.

1042
01:16:47,536 --> 01:16:49,800
Gotta catch one pheasant
at least.

1043
01:16:49,905 --> 01:16:53,102
Hey, uh...
Well, uh... You know.

1044
01:16:59,114 --> 01:17:01,981
Well, Dan,
what's the verdict?

1045
01:17:02,084 --> 01:17:04,985
I was just going over
the findings.

1046
01:17:05,087 --> 01:17:08,022
There's nothing organically
wrong with you, Cary.

1047
01:17:08,123 --> 01:17:10,182
Why do I have
these headaches?

1048
01:17:10,292 --> 01:17:14,353
It's not my imagination.
And they're getting worse all the time.

1049
01:17:14,463 --> 01:17:17,432
- You're punishing yourself.
- For what?

1050
01:17:17,532 --> 01:17:22,333
For running away from life. Headaches
are nature's way of making a protest.

1051
01:17:22,437 --> 01:17:25,736
Will you give me
something for them?

1052
01:17:25,841 --> 01:17:28,742
Do you expect me to give you
a prescription to cure life?

1053
01:17:28,844 --> 01:17:31,438
Sit down.
I want to talk to you.

1054
01:17:31,546 --> 01:17:33,571
Forget for a moment
that I'm your doctor.

1055
01:17:33,682 --> 01:17:37,174
Let me give you some advice
as a friend. Marry him.

1056
01:17:41,323 --> 01:17:44,554
Well, there's no point
in discussing that.

1057
01:17:44,660 --> 01:17:47,527
- It's all over.
- Apparently it isn't.

1058
01:17:47,629 --> 01:17:52,692
- You still have the headaches.
- But that's silly.

1059
01:17:52,801 --> 01:17:55,292
And anyway,
how could I marry him?

1060
01:17:55,404 --> 01:17:59,135
The whole thing was impossible
from the beginning.

1061
01:17:59,241 --> 01:18:03,610
You know, Dan, in a place like
Stoningham, you can't ignore convention.

1062
01:18:03,712 --> 01:18:07,808
So you gave up a man you were
in love with because of others?

1063
01:18:07,916 --> 01:18:10,282
And you had the great satisfaction
of being taken back into the fold.

1064
01:18:10,385 --> 01:18:12,512
I was thinking of my children.

1065
01:18:12,621 --> 01:18:15,954
You're just as lonely as you
were before. Lonelier, in fact,

1066
01:18:16,058 --> 01:18:18,458
with kay married
and ned abroad.

1067
01:18:18,560 --> 01:18:21,927
Sso what good
was your noble sacrifice?

1068
01:18:22,030 --> 01:18:24,021
Cary, marry him.

1069
01:18:25,634 --> 01:18:29,331
Oh, it... it's too late.

1070
01:18:30,439 --> 01:18:34,136
And maybe he's
found someone else.

1071
01:18:34,242 --> 01:18:38,144
Anyway, if he'd really loved me,
he would have come to me.

1072
01:18:38,246 --> 01:18:41,682
No! If you'd loved him,
you'd have gone to him!

1073
01:18:41,783 --> 01:18:44,684
In spite of the town,
the children, everything.

1074
01:18:44,786 --> 01:18:49,086
Let's face it. You were ready
for a love affair, but not for love.

1075
01:18:57,399 --> 01:18:59,663
Good-bye, Dan.

1076
01:19:10,212 --> 01:19:12,112
- Cary!
- Hello, Alida!

1077
01:19:15,751 --> 01:19:18,276
- It's so good to see you!
- It's so good to see you!

1078
01:19:18,386 --> 01:19:20,547
What were you doing in the doctor's
office? Nothing wrong, is there?

1079
01:19:20,655 --> 01:19:23,920
Oh, no. Just a checkup.
He couldn't find a thing wrong with me.

1080
01:19:24,025 --> 01:19:26,493
- Would you have a cup of tea?
- I'd love to, but I'm late.

1081
01:19:26,595 --> 01:19:29,655
- I have to pick up Mary Ann.
- Mary ann?

1082
01:19:29,765 --> 01:19:33,098
- She's getting married, you know.
- Married?

1083
01:19:33,201 --> 01:19:36,364
Very nice boy from new jersey. They've
been going together for a year now.

1084
01:19:36,471 --> 01:19:40,373
- I thought...
- I don't think you've met this one.

1085
01:19:40,475 --> 01:19:44,571
I have to dash. Come by and see us,
We miss you!

1086
01:19:44,679 --> 01:19:48,308
- I appreciate that. Good-bye, Alida.
- Bye!

1087
01:20:54,416 --> 01:20:55,906
Cary!

1088
01:22:27,809 --> 01:22:29,834
- Alida?
- Hello, Cary.

1089
01:22:29,945 --> 01:22:34,848
- Come on in.
- I thought i should come over.

1090
01:22:34,950 --> 01:22:38,249
- There's been an accident, Cary.
- It's ron.

1091
01:22:38,353 --> 01:22:40,446
- You better come with me.
- How bad is he?

1092
01:22:40,555 --> 01:22:42,819
Don't know yet.
Dr. Hennessy and Mick are with him now.

1093
01:22:42,924 --> 01:22:45,017
- Oh, alida.
- Get your coat first.

1094
01:22:45,126 --> 01:22:49,256
- I'll tell you on the way.
- [Footsteps Running]

1095
01:23:10,552 --> 01:23:12,918
Mrs. Scott.
Please, Mrs. Scott.

1096
01:23:13,021 --> 01:23:15,581
- How is he?
- We don't know anything yet.

1097
01:23:15,690 --> 01:23:18,557
- Where's Mr. Anderson?
- He took the doctor back to town.

1098
01:23:18,660 --> 01:23:21,561
- Well, didn't he...
- Nothing that he could have done.

1099
01:23:21,663 --> 01:23:24,598
He'll be back
in the morning.

1100
01:23:27,035 --> 01:23:30,596
I'm sorry, Mrs. Scott.
I have strict orders.

1101
01:23:30,705 --> 01:23:35,608
He can't be disturbed.
He must be kept quiet.

1102
01:23:35,710 --> 01:23:37,974
Let me take your coat.

1103
01:23:40,615 --> 01:23:43,516
Why don't you sit down?
I'll get some coffee.

1104
01:23:51,793 --> 01:23:54,387
Wish Mick had waited.

1105
01:23:54,496 --> 01:23:57,761
But I'm sure the doctor wouldn't have
gone if he thought there were...

1106
01:23:57,866 --> 01:24:00,357
Alida.

1107
01:24:07,509 --> 01:24:09,670
This room.

1108
01:24:10,779 --> 01:24:14,010
The beauty that
Ron's put into it.

1109
01:24:14,115 --> 01:24:16,015
And the love.

1110
01:24:16,117 --> 01:24:20,952
He never gave up hope
that you'd come back, Cary.

1111
01:24:29,030 --> 01:24:33,933
You told me once that
Ron was so secure within himself.

1112
01:24:34,035 --> 01:24:39,029
Because he refused to give importance
to unimportant things.

1113
01:24:39,140 --> 01:24:42,132
Why did it take me so long
to understand it?

1114
01:24:42,243 --> 01:24:46,703
Remember I told you it took us
a long time to find the right answer?

1115
01:24:46,815 --> 01:24:49,511
It doesn't happen overnight.

1116
01:24:55,857 --> 01:24:58,519
I feel like such a coward.

1117
01:24:58,626 --> 01:25:03,029
I was so frightened.
I let others make my decisions.

1118
01:25:04,766 --> 01:25:08,395
Alida, I've let so many people
come between us.

1119
01:25:08,503 --> 01:25:11,961
Friends, neighbors, children.

1120
01:25:12,073 --> 01:25:15,702
And the strangest one of all, myself.

1121
01:25:15,810 --> 01:25:18,335
Don't worry about things
in the past.

1122
01:25:18,446 --> 01:25:22,280
Isn't that
unimportant too, hmm?

1123
01:25:28,123 --> 01:25:31,092
If only I haven't
waited too long.

1124
01:25:31,192 --> 01:25:35,253
Mrs. Scott?
Your coffee.

1125
01:25:35,363 --> 01:25:38,457
Thank you, but I really
don't care for any.

1126
01:25:38,566 --> 01:25:41,797
Why don't you go upstairs
and rest a while? Try to sleep.

1127
01:25:41,903 --> 01:25:47,136
I couldn't sleep.
I want to stay here in case he wakes up.

1128
01:25:47,242 --> 01:25:49,836
May I sit over there?

1129
01:25:49,944 --> 01:25:52,913
Well, all right.

1130
01:26:33,555 --> 01:26:39,016
- Well, Dan?
- He's got a concussion.

1131
01:26:39,127 --> 01:26:42,290
- Of course not.
- Otherwise, I'd get him to the hospital.

1132
01:26:42,397 --> 01:26:45,525
It's gonna take time
for him to recover.

1133
01:26:45,633 --> 01:26:48,625
Dan, what can I do?

1134
01:26:48,736 --> 01:26:51,068
You plan to stay?

1135
01:26:51,172 --> 01:26:53,640
Yes. No more running away.

1136
01:26:53,741 --> 01:26:59,145
He'll need rest and care.
And he'll need you, CCary.

1137
01:27:00,381 --> 01:27:02,281
Nurse.

1138
01:27:49,097 --> 01:27:50,997
Cary.

1139
01:27:52,700 --> 01:27:55,225
Yes, Ron.

1140
01:27:56,371 --> 01:27:58,271
You've come home.

1141
01:28:00,108 --> 01:28:04,135
Yes, darling, I've...
I've come home.
